[30;1m11 | [0m[35mPng text chunk size limits[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m--------------------------[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mTo prevent potential denial of service attacks using compressed text[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mchunks, there are now limits to the decompressed size of text chunks[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mdecoded from PNG images. If the limits are exceeded when opening a PNG[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mimage a :py:exc:`ValueError` will be raised.[0m

[30;1m6350 | [0m[35m  have have been premultiplied with the alpha value.  PIL allows[0m

[30;1m5 | [0m[35m============[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mThe ``anchor`` parameter determines the alignment of drawn text relative to the ``xy`` parameter.[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35mThe default alignment is top left, specifically ``la`` (left-ascender) for horizontal text[0m
[30;1m9 | [0m[35mand ``lt`` (left-top) for vertical text.[0m
[30;1m10 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m11 | [0m[35mThis parameter is only supported by OpenType/TrueType fonts.[0m
